To convert to a credit union, the mutual association shall deliver to the Commissioner:
A written application for conversion in the form that the Department of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation requires;
Any additional exhibits the Department may require;
Any filing fee set by the Department by regulation; and
Its proposed amended articles and bylaws.

The examination shall include, but not be limited to, the following:
The financial history and condition of the mutual association including:
The identification of overvalued assets, undisclosed nonperforming loans, and understated liabilities;
The identification of assets that may become nonperforming assets upon conversion;
The identification of loans in default and loans past due over 60 days;
Review of material litigation affecting the mutual association, and the identification of significant judgments, orders or decrees affecting its financial status; and
Review of mortgage contracts, participating loans, and other commitments.
The management of the association.
